article.description: Frederick Scott scored 17 points, including the go-ahead bucket, and hauled in 10 rebounds to lead Rider to a 67-65 win over George Washington on Monday night.
article.headline: Scott lifts Rider to 67-65 win over George Washington
article.linkText: Scott lifts Rider to 67-65 win over George Washington
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Frederick Scott scored 17 points, including the go-ahead bucket, and hauled in 10 rebounds to lead Rider to a 67-65 win over George Washington on Monday night. Tied at 65 with under a minute to play, Scott got what would become the winning bucket with 36 seconds left and George Washington's Jair Bolden missed a 3-pointer at the other end just ahead of the buzzer. Stevie Jordan grabbed the defensive rebound to seal the win. Jordan Allen hit three 3-pointers and finished with 15 points and Jordan had 12 points for Rider (3-1), which got its first win over an Atlantic 10 opponent since 2010. George Washington (2-2) opened the second half with a 3-pointer from Terry Nolan Jr. to break a 32-all halftime tie but neither team could break away in a second half that included four lead changes. Patrick Steeves led the Colonials with 19 points and Yuta Watanabe added 16 points and had six of the team's 12 blocked shots.
